{"sha": "bb27781b64162e1769df15e0c97e8d2145d2d10d", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0MTM2NTMxMDA6YmIyNzc4MWI2NDE2MmUxNzY5ZGYxNWUwYzk3ZThkMjE0NWQyZDEwZA==", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2020-05-04T20:13:28Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2020-05-04T21:47:30Z"}, "message": "libstdc++: Fix incorrect size calculation in PMR resource  (PR 94906)\n\nCalculating the size of a chunk being returned to the upstream allocator\nwas done with a 32-bit type, so it wrapped if the chunk was 4GB or\nlarger.\n\nI don't know how to test this without allocating 4GB, so there's no test\nin the testsuite. It has been tested manually with allocations sizes and\nalignments exceeding 4GB.\n\n\tPR libstdc++/94906\n\t* src/c++17/memory_resource.cc\n\t(monotonic_buffer_resource::_Chunk::release): Use size_t for shift\n\toperands.", "tree": {"sha": "2c34c125e8275c26ac0ab02ca7b42ab2ad7bbd35", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/2c34c125e8275c26ac0ab02ca7b42ab2ad7bbd35"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/bb27781b64162e1769df15e0c97e8d2145d2d10d", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/bb27781b64162e1769df15e0c97e8d2145d2d10d", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/bb27781b64162e1769df15e0c97e8d2145d2d10d", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/bb27781b64162e1769df15e0c97e8d2145d2d10d/comments", "author": {"login": "jwakely", "id": 1254480, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTQ0ODA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1254480?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely", "html_url": "https://github.com/jwakely", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/user